                <html:p>
  In contrast, there exist non-initial integral Heyting algebras (e.g. non-trivial linear Heyting algebras are integral). However, free Heyting algebras, except <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[2]]></fr:tex>, are not integral, but they will be <html:em><fr:link href="/idem-comm-75C1/" title="Local distributive lattice" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-75C1/" display-uri="idem-comm-75C1" type="local">local</fr:link></html:em>. For instance, the spectrum <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec}\mathbb {H}[x]]]></fr:tex> in <fr:link href="/schm-LRJP/" title="The Rieger-Nishimura scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-LRJP/" display-uri="schm-LRJP" type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-LRJP/" display-uri="schm-LRJP" /></fr:link> has two irreducible components, corresponding to the two maximal points.
